commit 5d319c5989d599e9e867df76795eb81472b4db7a
Author: Matthias Clasen <mclasen@redhat.com>
Date:   Thu Aug 28 01:19:29 2014 -0400

    Add tests for pango markup

    This test is modeled after the GMarkup parser tests in GLib.
    Test file with a name ending in .markup can be dumped in
    tests/markups/, and tests/markup-parse can be used to generate
    the expected output files which should be in the same location
    and with the extension .markup replaced by .expected.

    The test is also used as an installed test.

 tests/Makefile.am              |  18 ++-
 tests/markup-parse.c           | 249
 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 tests/markups/fail-1.expected  |   1 +
 tests/markups/fail-1.markup    |   1 +
 tests/markups/valid-1.expected |  12 ++
 tests/markups/valid-1.markup   |   1 +
 tests/markups/valid-2.expected |  12 ++
 tests/markups/valid-2.markup   |   1 +
 tests/markups/valid-3.expected |  18 +++
 tests/markups/valid-3.markup   |  11 ++
 tests/markups/valid-4.expected |  38 +++++++
 tests/markups/valid-4.markup   |   1 +
 12 files changed, 360 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

